&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse, Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crawley Day Surgery Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Crawley Day Surgery Unit is part of Surrey and Sussex Healthcare Trust which has been awarded Outstanding by the CQC and consistently ranked in the top 20% nationally for staff recommending the Trust as a place to work or receive treatment. This is a great opportunity for an experienced or new qualified Nurse or Operating Department Practitioner to be part of a supportive and forward thinking day surgery team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are 2 ward areas and 4 theatres in the unit operating Monday - Friday and we cover the following specialities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ophthalmology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gynaecology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ENT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orthopaedics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Urology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on supporting staff through professional development with a clear rotation scheme through all specialities as well as formal educational courses through local universities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like an informal visit or further information please contact Carlos Miras, Ward Manager (carlos.miras-sampedro@nhs.net or 01737 768511 x 6280).&lt;/p&gt;
